  <title>Gio.File.new_for_path</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function new_for_path(path: String): <link xref="Gio.File">Gio.File</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_file_new_for_path()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Constructs a <link xref="Gio.File"/> for a given path. This operation never
fails, but the returned object might not support any I/O
operation if <code>path</code> is malformed.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>path</code></title>
  <p>a string containing a relative or absolute path.
    The string must be encoded in the glib filename encoding.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>a new <link xref="Gio.File"/> for the given <code>path</code>.
  Free the returned object with <link href="../GObject-2.0/GObject.Object.unref.html">GObject.Object.prototype.unref</link>.</p>
</item>
</terms>

